text: Helen Ione White (born ) is a New Zealand politician. In 2020 she became a Member of Parliament in the House of Representatives for the Labour Party. In 2023, she was chosen by Labour to run for the Mount Albert electorate. White won the seat, holding it for Labour, but won the election by 18 votes. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:New Zealand politicians Category:New Zealand lawyers Category:1960s births
